definitions.definition: Without signs and symptoms that are detectable by physical examination or laboratory test; not clinically manifest.
examples: Some conditions may remain subclinical until they resolve without intervention, whereas others worsen from subclinical to clinical status.
definitions.label_groups: medicine , of a disease or injury

definitions.definition: Where some criteria are met but not enough to reach the status of a clinical diagnosis .
Less than is needed for clinical reasons.
examples: Off-label use of certain drugs at subclinical dosages has been a theme in realms of activity such as metabolic optimization, weight loss, body hacking, and neurohacking (e.g., nootropics); such drugs include metformin, beta-blockers, and others.

main_definition: ( medicine , of a disease or injury ) Without signs and symptoms that are detectable by physical examination or laboratory test; not clinically manifest.
secondary_definitions: ( medicine , in diagnosis ) Where some criteria are met but not enough to reach the status of a clinical diagnosis .
( medicine , of a dosage ) Less than is needed for clinical reasons.
